  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-20",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-20",
  "description": "An Estoppel is a quadruple (Q, R, ρ, δ) — a party Q whose position is being estopped, a relying party R who changed their position based on Q's prior representation ρ, and the detriment δ R would suffer if Q were now permitted to assert their actual position. The defining structure: estoppel does not extinguish Q's right (contrast with waiver) but blocks the path from Q's right C ∈ H_{t*} to the settled layer H*_{t*} within this forum — the forum's σ-nucleus refuses to process Q's claim because the contextual condition (R's reliance to their detriment) makes settlement of C inequitable. Formally: a nucleus-blocking condition imposed by the forum's site topology J — estoppel is a local sieve that prevents Q's claim from covering, not a retraction of the claim from the fiber.",
  "isPartOf": {
